{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 53 "I.  a.  What is the defin
ition of a \"prime number\"?  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 100 "          A prime number is a positive i
nteger (greater than 1) whose only factors are 1 and itself." }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 98 "    b1.  Use Ma
ple to determine whether there are 5 primes in the range 1 - 29.  Yes,
 more than 5." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 57 "for k from \+
1 to 29 do if isprime(k) then print (k) fi od;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
